One of the many reasons why a full and comprehensive exam is THE protocol of care @tksoptometrists Posted @withrepost ‚Ä¢ @optomegeek This beast was taken with our #Optos California using steering. The original image just caught the tip, and could have been written off as an artefact (lots of lashes and lid in the way)if I had not also had a look with my slit lamp and #volk. This was something that was way out of my comfort zone, so promptly referred to Medical Retina for further assessment.  This patient is currently being monitored.
However, this reminded me of the useful learning pneumonic -
‚ÄúTo Find a Small Ocular Melanoma Using Helpful Hints Daily‚Äù

Thickness - >2mm with ultrasound
Fluid - sub retinal with OCT)
Symptoms - decreased vision, flashes, floaters
Orange - Lipofuscin
Margin within 3mm of ONH
Ultra sonographic Hollowness
H - absence of Halo
D -  Absence of Drusen

If 1 or 2 of these are present then monitoring is suggested. 
If 3 or more is present, then malignancy should be expected and treated accordingly.
